In a recent statement from the Oval Office, President Trump announced that Nikki Haley will be leaving her position as the U.S. Ambassador to the United Nations at the end of the year. He praised her for her hard work and accomplishments, including the successful negotiations with North Korea and the withdrawal from the Iran nuclear deal. Haley expressed her gratitude for the opportunity to serve and highlighted the progress made by the United States in foreign policy during her tenure. The President also mentioned that a successor will be named within the next few weeks.